WEBVTT

00:08.842 --> 00:10.051
[Justine] <i>It's a million degrees in here.</i>

00:10.135 --> 00:11.553
-[Sam] <i>It's not that bad.</i>
-[Justine] <i>Yes, it is.</i>

00:11.928 --> 00:14.139
-You’re sweating. Like, a lot.
-Huh?

00:14.889 --> 00:17.308
Well, yeah,
the fucking air conditioner's broken.

00:17.392 --> 00:18.768
-[presses buttons]
-Well, maybe roll down

00:18.852 --> 00:20.061
all the windows, then.<i> </i>

00:20.145 --> 00:22.439
[sighs]
All right, listen, when we go in there,

00:22.522 --> 00:24.190
don’t make too much small talk.

00:24.399 --> 00:26.192
-I’m not gonna say anything.
-Well, no.

00:26.276 --> 00:28.737
I mean, [stammers]
you gotta say something, but...

00:28.903 --> 00:30.321
J-Just be yourself.

00:30.905 --> 00:33.199
You know, maybe ten percent less weird.
That would be good.

00:33.491 --> 00:34.909
Wow. Okay, thanks.

00:34.993 --> 00:37.287
You know what I'm saying.
I mean, it's just...

00:37.787 --> 00:40.081
I--
I need you to look like you give a shit.

00:40.582 --> 00:42.083
I give a shit.

00:42.167 --> 00:44.919
It’s summer vacation,
and I’m not backpacking through Europe.

00:45.003 --> 00:46.004
I’m here.

00:46.838 --> 00:47.881
I really want this.

00:48.173 --> 00:50.925
All right, okay.
All right. But don't want it too much.

00:51.009 --> 00:53.720
You know what I mean? Don't...
You don't wanna appear desperate.

00:57.474 --> 01:00.268
Christ, I haven't been here
in a long time.

01:01.811 --> 01:02.645
Hey.

01:02.896 --> 01:05.440
Uh, Sam Sylvia, Justine Biagi.

01:05.774 --> 01:09.235
[guard] Yes, sir. Please pull forward
and park in any of the visitors spaces.

01:09.360 --> 01:11.071
[Sam] Okay, here we go.

01:11.154 --> 01:14.407
Happy fucking faces. Happy faces.

01:14.949 --> 01:17.994
Not too happy. Not... Okay.

01:18.078 --> 01:22.373
[uplifting rock music playing]

01:22.707 --> 01:25.794
Ah. How about this one?
Reserved, but still fun.

01:25.877 --> 01:27.337
No! [grunts]

01:27.420 --> 01:29.631
-What's wrong with pigs?
-She hates animals.

01:29.714 --> 01:31.049
So, no leopard print, then?

01:31.132 --> 01:32.550
-Where--
-[knocking at door]

01:32.675 --> 01:34.761
[takes a deep breath] Fuck.

01:37.514 --> 01:39.057
Hi, Birdie. [clears throat]

01:39.682 --> 01:41.976
There is a water feature in the kitchen.

01:43.686 --> 01:47.065
It’s a hot tub. [chuckles]
They’re standard in all the penthouses.

01:47.440 --> 01:48.483
Please, come in.

01:49.067 --> 01:50.944
Careful making toast.

01:51.111 --> 01:53.947
Well, we mostly order room service.
It's free.

01:54.572 --> 01:55.907
-Mostly.
-[door closes]

01:56.658 --> 01:58.618
[Bash, in hoarse voice]
Where are you staying?

01:58.868 --> 02:01.913
At the Sands.
What’s the matter with your voice?

02:02.163 --> 02:03.790
Oh, Bash is on vocal rest.

02:03.873 --> 02:07.585
He basically yells for an hour straight
every night, and the audience loves him.

02:07.669 --> 02:10.130
-But it’s very hard on his vocal chords.
-[quietly] Very hard.

02:10.296 --> 02:13.883
Oh. So you speak <i>for </i>him.

02:14.843 --> 02:16.553
Oh! Rhonda. [chuckles]

02:17.470 --> 02:19.097
Rhonda Howard.

02:20.849 --> 02:23.643
-I'm sorry I didn’t say anything sooner.
-No, I'm fine.

02:23.726 --> 02:26.187
I mean, what mother doesn’t want to learn
from American Express

02:26.271 --> 02:28.022
that her son has married a new cardholder?

02:28.439 --> 02:30.066
And there's why
I didn't say anything sooner.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.776
[Birdie] Oh, save your voice, Romeo.

02:31.860 --> 02:36.030
I’m simply here to meet the woman
that my son fell so madly in love with

02:36.114 --> 02:39.075
that he kept her a secret from his family.

02:39.325 --> 02:40.994
Well, maybe this is a good thing.

02:41.369 --> 02:44.706
Because I don't like secrets.
And I've been wanting to meet you, too,

02:44.789 --> 02:45.999
-Mom.
-No, no.

02:46.207 --> 02:47.625
-Mrs. Howard.
-[Bash] Uh-uh.

02:48.001 --> 02:49.419
-[whispers] Birdie.
-Birdie.

02:50.587 --> 02:53.715
[takes a deep breath] Let's order lunch.

02:54.716 --> 02:55.967
And drinks.

02:57.010 --> 03:00.096
[woman]
So... I'm just gonna come out and say it.

03:01.181 --> 03:04.350
We are very interested in this.

03:04.809 --> 03:07.145
I do have a couple of thoughts,
mostly questions.

03:07.228 --> 03:09.647
-Uh, uh, yeah. Of course, go ahead. Shoot.
-[bag unzips]

03:09.731 --> 03:11.774
-[clears throat]
-[woman] So, my first question...

03:12.150 --> 03:13.985
what do you think of Michael J. Fox?

03:14.152 --> 03:15.069
Uh...

03:15.153 --> 03:16.321
He's great. Yeah.

03:16.404 --> 03:17.864
For what? For-- For the dad?

03:18.239 --> 03:19.282
He’s a little young.

03:19.574 --> 03:20.783
No, I mean for Jules.

03:21.492 --> 03:23.536
But, uh, Jules is a girl.

03:23.620 --> 03:25.663
[woman] Well, in this draft, sure,
but, you know,

03:25.747 --> 03:28.041
I've worked with Michael,
and he is one of the nicest,

03:28.124 --> 03:29.751
most down-to-earth people.

03:29.834 --> 03:31.461
And he's mid-20s, but he plays young.

03:32.295 --> 03:33.129
Okay.

03:35.465 --> 03:39.135
Uh, my next question:
The title... are we married to it?

03:40.929 --> 03:44.098
[Debbie] Want me to throw it back?
Yeah! I'll throw it back.

03:44.182 --> 03:45.850
-I'll throw it. Throw it.
-[blows raspberry]

03:45.934 --> 03:48.603
Oh, thank you. That was mean.

03:48.895 --> 03:50.521
-[door opens]
-[chuckles]

03:51.564 --> 03:52.398
-Oh, hi.
-Hey.

03:52.482 --> 03:54.484
I’ve got, um, paychecks.

03:54.567 --> 03:57.820
-[Randy giggling and babbling]
-Oh!

03:57.904 --> 04:00.657
-[Debbie] Oh, my God. Okay. I gotta...
-Can I talk to you?

04:00.907 --> 04:02.200
Yes. Uh...

04:02.283 --> 04:06.496
Okay, we're gonna have to do it out here
because I-- I now live in the hallway.

04:06.579 --> 04:07.830
That's all Randy wants to do.

04:07.914 --> 04:10.750
An entire fucking hotel playhouse,
and we’re just in the hallway.

04:10.833 --> 04:12.835
So, have a seat. Welcome to my office.

04:13.419 --> 04:14.545
What can I do for you?

04:14.629 --> 04:16.297
-[Jenny] Thank you.
-Here's your paycheck.

04:16.464 --> 04:17.423
[Jenny] Um...

04:17.507 --> 04:18.466
Okay.

04:18.549 --> 04:21.803
I have been reviewing my finances

04:21.886 --> 04:24.055
and speaking to, uh,

04:24.138 --> 04:26.140
other costume designers
on the Strip,

04:26.224 --> 04:29.686
who were surprised to find out
that I am not being compensated

04:29.769 --> 04:31.396
for my additional wardrobe work.

04:31.479 --> 04:34.983
You-- What? We don’t pay you
for your additional wardrobe work?

04:35.275 --> 04:38.903
You do not.
And I know I’m not Bob Mackie, or...

04:39.237 --> 04:41.572
Pete Menefee, or Michael Travis,

04:41.656 --> 04:45.076
but all of the costumes
require maintenance

04:45.159 --> 04:46.244
and doubles,

04:46.327 --> 04:49.872
and my goal is to leave here
with as much money as possible

04:49.956 --> 04:52.083
without spending one more cent
at this hotel,

04:52.166 --> 04:53.584
because it offends me to my core.

04:53.668 --> 04:55.670
[Randy cooing]

04:55.962 --> 05:01.092
So, uh, how much of a weekly increase
would that be... exactly?

05:01.968 --> 05:04.095
I believe a...

05:04.887 --> 05:07.432
13 percent jump would be reasonable,

05:07.515 --> 05:08.766
given my research.

05:09.142 --> 05:10.768
And I will accept nothing less,

05:10.852 --> 05:13.563
or will cease my responsibilities
henceforth immediately.

05:14.397 --> 05:15.231
Okay.

05:16.065 --> 05:17.025
Um...

05:17.483 --> 05:19.610
I will see what I can do.
Thank you, Jenny.

05:19.694 --> 05:21.779
-I'm glad you came to me.
-[Jenny] You are?

05:22.322 --> 05:23.156
[Debbie] Yeah.

05:23.406 --> 05:24.741
[sighs]

05:25.366 --> 05:28.119
-I was pretty nervous.
-You did so well, I couldn't tell at all.

05:28.202 --> 05:29.203
-Really?
-[Debbie] Yeah.

05:29.287 --> 05:30.538
-Wow, great.
-[gasps]

05:31.372 --> 05:33.249
Where the fuck is Randy? Randy?

05:33.583 --> 05:34.417
Randy?

05:34.500 --> 05:35.835
-[Dawn] We got him!
-[Randy laughs]

05:35.918 --> 05:39.464
Oh, you love Dawn and Stacey, don't you?

05:39.547 --> 05:40.882
[Stacey] Yes, you did so good...

05:41.424 --> 05:42.633
-Oh!
-Hi!

05:42.717 --> 05:44.635
[Stacey] I know you stopped breastfeeding
a while ago,

05:44.719 --> 05:46.637
but this kid's still got a thing for tits.

05:46.721 --> 05:49.766
-What can I say? He's a Vegas baby now.
-[Dawn and Stacey laugh]

05:50.183 --> 05:52.769
I mean, we've broken up before, but...

05:53.144 --> 05:54.854
I think it's for real this time.

05:55.271 --> 05:57.607
I can't eat anything. I can't sleep.

05:57.899 --> 06:00.818
-I start crying at the weirdest times.
-[croupier] Place your bet.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.112
I don't have anyone to talk to about it.

06:03.196 --> 06:05.656
Because the person I want to talk to
about it is Yolanda,

06:05.740 --> 06:08.284
and I can't talk to her about it,
you know?

06:08.368 --> 06:09.869
-[croupier] No more bets.
-No, not really.

06:11.245 --> 06:12.372
[croupier] Hard six.

06:12.538 --> 06:13.623
Six. You win.

06:14.374 --> 06:15.958
But you and Keith...

06:16.125 --> 06:17.251
We’re still married.

06:17.585 --> 06:20.129
He’s in LA, working.
I’m in Vegas, working. The end.

06:21.297 --> 06:22.590
Press on my five and ten?

06:23.674 --> 06:25.885
-Place your bets.
-Oh, I'm out.

06:26.344 --> 06:27.220
Where you going?

06:27.804 --> 06:30.890
I made a deal with myself I would
only spend $20 of my paycheck.

06:30.973 --> 06:32.850
[sighs] I'm gonna go eat.

06:33.518 --> 06:34.435
Alone.

06:36.270 --> 06:37.438
[scoffs]

06:38.981 --> 06:40.274
People have to eat.

06:41.234 --> 06:43.111
You know, I hate eating alone.

06:43.194 --> 06:44.904
You know, people say bring a book.

06:45.279 --> 06:47.407
Sit at the bar. I can't do it.

06:47.949 --> 06:50.243
Right now, I just wanna be alone
with a bunch of people.

06:50.326 --> 06:51.577
That's why I like craps.

06:51.661 --> 06:53.538
That’s why a lot of people like craps.

06:53.788 --> 06:54.956
-You ever play?
-Oh, no.

06:55.039 --> 06:57.208
I can't gamble here,
it's against the rules.

06:57.583 --> 07:00.461
And I'm a little bit of a scaredy-cat
when it comes to taking risks, so...

07:00.837 --> 07:04.924
[sighs] Well, I got four letters
from my husband I'm too scared to open.

07:05.341 --> 07:06.926
We're all afraid of something, Rita.

07:08.970 --> 07:10.555
[Birdie] So, Rhonda...

07:11.222 --> 07:12.932
you're from England.

07:13.516 --> 07:14.559
What gave it away?

07:14.642 --> 07:18.146
-[Rhonda and Bash chuckle]
-[Birdie laughs exaggeratedly]

07:19.355 --> 07:20.356
London?

07:20.982 --> 07:23.234
-Bromley.
-Suburbs.

07:24.068 --> 07:25.736
Aren’t the suburbs in England,

07:25.820 --> 07:28.448
how do you say it...
[in English accent] a bit dodgy?

07:28.656 --> 07:30.074
[laughs]

07:30.408 --> 07:32.452
They are. That's why I left.

07:32.952 --> 07:35.955
And how long have you been
in <i>our </i>fine country?

07:36.038 --> 07:36.873
Um...

07:37.623 --> 07:38.541
Three years.

07:39.000 --> 07:41.294
-Do you know the band Duran Duran?
-Very popular.

07:42.003 --> 07:43.171
[Rhonda] They were touring the States,

07:43.254 --> 07:45.798
and they asked me and my mate
if we wanted to come, and we were like,

07:45.882 --> 07:47.258
"Uh, yeah." [chuckles]

07:47.425 --> 07:48.259
Flew private.

07:48.801 --> 07:50.219
See, I wanna be a singer,

07:50.303 --> 07:52.930
and I knew if I stayed in the UK,
I’d never be discovered.

07:53.306 --> 07:55.933
So, when the tour came to LA,
I decided to stay.

07:56.601 --> 07:58.644
It was really hard at first.
But I stuck it out.

07:59.353 --> 08:02.732
And I’m so glad I did because, otherwise,
I never would’ve been desperate enough

08:02.815 --> 08:05.818
to try out for <i>GLOW</i>
and meet this brilliant man.

08:06.235 --> 08:07.570
-[chuckles]
-Oh!

08:07.653 --> 08:09.947
Okay, so you're on the show.

08:10.406 --> 08:13.534
See, here I was thinking that
the two of you met...

08:14.452 --> 08:17.330
-what, in an alley somewhere?
-[all laugh]

08:17.413 --> 08:19.248
-Well, I did live in my car.
-[Birdie] Did you?

08:19.332 --> 08:20.416
Let's not...

08:21.584 --> 08:22.919
[coughs] Are you leaving?

08:23.628 --> 08:24.837
No, I'm not leaving.

08:25.505 --> 08:29.217
I was thinking that we...
should go shopping.

08:31.219 --> 08:32.053
We should?

08:32.136 --> 08:33.888
[Birdie] We should!
You're married to my son,

08:33.971 --> 08:37.266
and I haven't even gotten you
a wedding present.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.352
-Well, I'll come.
-[Birdie] Nonsense.

08:40.061 --> 08:42.063
Oh, don't worry, I won't bite.

08:42.647 --> 08:46.943
I just wanna get to know
my daughter-in-law, one-on-one.

08:47.276 --> 08:48.778
Just us girls.

08:51.447 --> 08:54.200
I mean, it wouldn’t be the worst thing
in the world if Jules was a boy.

08:54.283 --> 08:55.743
In a David Bowie kind of way.

08:55.826 --> 08:57.328
It's a terrible idea.

08:57.411 --> 08:59.664
-You said it was interesting.
-Yeah, by “interesting,”

08:59.747 --> 09:00.915
I meant fucking stupid.

09:00.998 --> 09:04.001
I was just being polite
because she's a woman, you know?

09:04.085 --> 09:07.088
I mean, she had every other page
of your script crossed out.

09:07.296 --> 09:10.007
You know, you don't have to have a penis
to be a fucking asshole.

09:12.093 --> 09:14.053
Oh, that's another thing.
When they're giving their stupid notes,

09:14.136 --> 09:16.889
don’t take out your little notebook.
It's just gonna get you more notes.

09:18.432 --> 09:21.394
Okay. Well...
what's the deal with this guy?

09:21.477 --> 09:23.563
Don Silverberg. We go way back.

09:23.646 --> 09:25.106
I gave him his first job.

09:25.940 --> 09:29.694
So, hopefully, there's a little juice here
for me, and this will go a lot better.

09:32.446 --> 09:33.698
Sam Sylvia.

09:34.657 --> 09:37.118
-I kept you waiting.
-All right, all right!

09:37.618 --> 09:39.662
Don! How are ya?

09:41.789 --> 09:43.666
Okay. What,
are you a fucking Buddhist now?

09:43.833 --> 09:44.667
I am.

09:45.459 --> 09:46.419
All right.

09:46.502 --> 09:47.920
You... You know what?

09:48.004 --> 09:49.964
-You remember the last time I saw you?
-Mm.

09:50.047 --> 09:52.592
-I was drunk. It was at that pool party.
-[Don] Mm-hmm.

09:52.675 --> 09:55.344
And Bryan and his guys
were making you shave their asses

09:55.428 --> 09:56.304
because they thought

09:56.387 --> 09:57.805
-it would make 'em swim faster.
-[Don] Ah.

09:57.888 --> 09:59.348
[Don and Sam chuckle]

09:59.432 --> 10:01.642
Yeah, that isn't the last time
I saw you, Sam, but...

10:01.726 --> 10:03.978
I am not surprised
you don't remember that.

10:05.146 --> 10:08.024
All right, so let’s, uh,
let's skip the pleasantries, all right?

10:08.107 --> 10:11.569
My kid wrote a great script. I know that,
you know that. That's why we're here.

10:11.819 --> 10:12.737
I didn't read it.

10:14.071 --> 10:16.365
Okay, well,
we can walk you through the story.

10:16.449 --> 10:19.327
No, no, no, no, no. No, I just want
to know if the rumors are true.

10:20.494 --> 10:22.204
You're... directing porn now?

10:23.080 --> 10:24.165
No, it's not porn.

10:24.248 --> 10:28.085
It's women's wrestling, but, hey, as long
as people are still talking, right?

10:28.169 --> 10:29.128
They're not.

10:29.503 --> 10:31.088
