the more expensive one

13:06.118 --> 13:08.078
because it's more posh, but...

13:08.954 --> 13:11.707
I'm gonna go with this one
because I actually like it more.

13:15.586 --> 13:17.004
Interesting.

13:21.801 --> 13:23.594
[dress unzipping]

13:25.930 --> 13:26.764
[Rhonda sighs]

13:29.058 --> 13:29.934
Look...

13:30.434 --> 13:33.145
Bash told me to be scared of you,
and I am...

13:33.979 --> 13:36.524
but I also want to be honest with you.

13:39.610 --> 13:41.362
I married Bash for the wrong reasons.

13:41.529 --> 13:42.738
[sighs in exasperation]

13:42.822 --> 13:46.116
God, you're taking all the fun
out of this whole thing.

13:46.617 --> 13:50.246
Although I do appreciate you
not wasting my time.

13:51.163 --> 13:52.623
Okay, let's hear it.

13:53.833 --> 13:55.668
Okay, so...

13:56.335 --> 13:59.129
when Bash asked me to marry him,
I didn't love him.

14:00.214 --> 14:02.216
I didn't really even know him.

14:03.551 --> 14:05.052
I married Bash because...

14:07.596 --> 14:08.806
I needed a green card.

14:08.889 --> 14:12.935
You married my son
because you needed... a green card?

14:13.143 --> 14:16.689
[sighs] I know. I know it's awful,
but I love him now.

14:16.897 --> 14:18.065
I fell in love with him.

14:18.148 --> 14:21.861
Right, well, it's not hard
to fall in love with a millionaire.

14:23.445 --> 14:24.488
Maybe not.

14:24.947 --> 14:28.367
But... Bash is kind, and caring,

14:28.993 --> 14:31.161
and genuinely clever.

14:32.121 --> 14:36.000
[sighs] But he's also compulsive
and so innocent sometimes,

14:36.083 --> 14:37.793
it hurts to look at him, you know?

14:38.335 --> 14:41.547
And I see all these people
just wanting to take advantage of him

14:41.630 --> 14:44.592
and his generosity because all they see
is his money. And I--

14:44.675 --> 14:47.553
And I'm supposed to believe
that <i>you </i>don't.

14:49.054 --> 14:52.099
That you're not just gonna walk away
with all his money.

14:52.892 --> 14:53.893
[exhales]

14:54.852 --> 14:55.811
The other day...

14:56.228 --> 14:59.440
I saw all these unopened checks
just laying around the penthouse.

14:59.899 --> 15:01.817
And I asked Bash
why he didn’t deposit them,

15:01.901 --> 15:03.569
and he said he didn’t know how.

15:04.820 --> 15:08.240
So I went down to the Clark County
Credit Union, and I did it for him.

15:08.324 --> 15:12.286
And I put his paychecks into savings
so he can’t spend it.

15:13.370 --> 15:15.289
I’m not even sure he knew he got paid.

15:17.583 --> 15:19.668
[scoffs] So...

15:20.586 --> 15:23.130
you don't trust my son...

15:24.173 --> 15:27.134
-with money.
-Well, he's not good with it.

15:28.928 --> 15:31.680
But... no one has to be good
at everything.

15:38.062 --> 15:40.105
Oh, he didn't even get you a diamond.

15:40.439 --> 15:43.275
Oh, no, I picked that. I like blue.

15:43.567 --> 15:44.735
Well, I hate it.

15:46.862 --> 15:47.821
[laughs]

15:47.905 --> 15:49.198
[wails]

15:49.281 --> 15:51.283
[Debbie] Okay. I know. I know.

15:51.367 --> 15:53.953
I'm sorry. Sorry. Honey. I know, sweetie.

15:54.036 --> 15:56.538
You okay? I guess you have two of them.
Um...

15:56.622 --> 15:58.374
He's better in the hallway.

15:59.291 --> 16:00.209
Hey, bud.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.337
Hey, bud, look! It's okay.

16:03.420 --> 16:04.380
[footsteps fading]

16:04.463 --> 16:07.383
Um, I also have a check for Sam.

16:07.466 --> 16:12.179
Uh, is it my job now to send him the money
he somehow still collects

16:12.262 --> 16:13.847
while I'm here working?

16:16.392 --> 16:17.226
Great.

16:17.309 --> 16:19.770
Um, also, uh, Jenny came to me today

16:19.853 --> 16:22.856
with what I think is
a very reasonable request for a raise.

16:22.940 --> 16:24.900
Um, I went through the budget
that you and Sam made,

16:24.984 --> 16:27.987
and I found the money in what appears
to be a line item

16:28.070 --> 16:30.531
for cigarettes and Dr. Pepper.

16:32.658 --> 16:33.784
[scoffs]

16:36.078 --> 16:37.121
What's happening?

16:45.546 --> 16:49.049
"Fine with Jenny raise.
Not wasting my voice on this."

16:51.719 --> 16:52.803
Do you have a sore throat?

16:54.054 --> 16:57.474
I'm sorr-- Please, rest your voice.
That's so smart. In fact, you know what?

16:57.558 --> 17:00.185
You don't have to talk at all.
I'll just... What I wanna say is this:

17:00.269 --> 17:03.147
Um, you are a dickhead,
and I don't trust you anymore.

17:03.230 --> 17:04.565
And Sam may have run off to LA,

17:04.648 --> 17:06.692
but I am still here.
And I brought my fucking kid.

17:06.775 --> 17:09.528
So there's not a single day
I will not be in your face.

17:09.611 --> 17:13.574
[loudly]
And I have very strong vocal chords!

17:14.408 --> 17:15.242
[exhales]

17:20.622 --> 17:22.624
I wish more men would go on vocal rest.

17:24.001 --> 17:25.252
Randy, it's time to go!

17:29.631 --> 17:30.591
Oh, my God.

17:31.091 --> 17:34.178
[up-tempo electronic music playing]

17:37.598 --> 17:39.600
[Randy blows raspberry]

17:56.450 --> 17:57.951
[grunts] Oh, hey there.

17:58.202 --> 17:59.244
Ooh!

17:59.495 --> 18:01.872
Hey, big spender. You with somebody?
You looking to get lucky

18:01.955 --> 18:03.999
-like the rest of us? Okay.
-[man] Sir.

18:04.083 --> 18:05.959
You can’t have a baby on the casino floor.

18:06.043 --> 18:07.336
That's why I picked him up.

18:07.419 --> 18:10.214
-Oh, I got you, sweetheart. Okay, buddy.
-[Randy wails]

18:11.465 --> 18:14.426
-Oh, my God! There he is! I'm so sorry.
-[man 2] It's okay.

18:14.510 --> 18:17.846
So sorry! Oh, my God.
He just got on the elevator.

18:17.930 --> 18:20.474
I was right there and then, boom,
the doors just closed.

18:21.183 --> 18:24.436
Hey, I know you.
You were on my 11:40 flight.

18:25.395 --> 18:27.106
Oh, yeah. Didn't you have a beard?

18:27.439 --> 18:30.234
-Uh, yeah. Turned in my hobo card.
-[both chuckle]

18:30.317 --> 18:33.320
I vaguely remember losing my cool
in front of you.

18:33.612 --> 18:36.740
-Unlike, say, now.
-You know, I haven't seen you in a while.

18:37.741 --> 18:41.203
Yeah, well, I... Because I made
the very smart decision to, um...

18:41.578 --> 18:44.081
bring my baby to the casino where I work.

18:44.164 --> 18:47.251
And, as you can see,
it's going exactly according to plan.

18:47.334 --> 18:48.544
[both laugh]

18:48.627 --> 18:50.587
-Thank you for finding him.
-You're welcome.

18:50.671 --> 18:53.757
Um, can I buy you a,
uh, "thank you" drink?

18:54.842 --> 18:57.845
How about I buy you
a "you're welcome" dinner instead?

18:58.679 --> 19:01.014
Are you asking me on a date while I...
[chuckles]

19:01.098 --> 19:03.350
...am holding my screaming son
in a casino?

19:03.433 --> 19:05.811
Yeah. You got a good babysitter?

19:05.894 --> 19:06.728
Um...

19:07.563 --> 19:09.773
Yeah. I’ve got some options.

19:10.023 --> 19:11.900
All right, I'll pick you up at 8:00.

19:12.734 --> 19:14.736
-Uh-huh.
-[Randy continues shrieking]

19:20.367 --> 19:22.369
Should you be smoking in here?

19:22.870 --> 19:23.954
There's an ashtray.

19:25.038 --> 19:27.374
-I think that's an award.
-[door opens]

19:28.000 --> 19:30.043
[man] Hi, sorry to keep you waiting. Hi.

19:30.669 --> 19:31.628
Jonathan.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.922
Hi. Hi.

19:37.593 --> 19:38.844
Yeah, I’m Sam.

19:38.927 --> 19:40.596
Uh, this is my daughter, Justine.

19:40.679 --> 19:42.389
She wrote a... good script.

19:42.472 --> 19:44.474
It’s, uh, you know, it's a very...

19:45.058 --> 19:46.351
personal, uh...

19:47.060 --> 19:50.022
You know what, she'll tell you.
She'll tell you.

19:53.150 --> 19:54.026
Um...

19:55.027 --> 19:56.820
Uh, sure, yeah. Uh...

19:57.696 --> 20:00.657
Well, the character is kinda based on me.

20:00.741 --> 20:01.700
Um...

20:02.618 --> 20:05.037
About a year ago,
I moved out here to Hollywood

20:05.120 --> 20:07.122
to meet my father for the first time.

20:07.206 --> 20:08.123
Only...

20:08.498 --> 20:11.001
-he didn't know he had a daughter.
-Shit.

20:11.668 --> 20:13.295
Yeah. It was weird.

20:13.587 --> 20:17.299
And all I knew were his movies,
which I worshiped.

20:17.758 --> 20:19.968
And, you know, he didn't know
what to do with me 'cause...

20:20.052 --> 20:23.597
what 50-year-old man wants
a teenage daughter dropped on them? So...

20:24.223 --> 20:26.892
he made me enroll in high school, and...

20:27.601 --> 20:30.687
basically the only way I survived, really,

20:31.146 --> 20:34.441
was because I met this group
of AV club nerds.

20:34.524 --> 20:37.110
And... they weren't the kind of nerds

20:37.194 --> 20:40.030
who were trying to get laid
by the hot girls. They were these...

20:40.656 --> 20:43.951
[sighs] ...weird, complicated kids,

20:44.034 --> 20:46.036
who were trying to make these...

20:46.119 --> 20:50.207
little movies in a-- in a town of people
trying to make big movies.

20:50.290 --> 20:53.543
And that made me think
about how weird it is to grow up

20:53.627 --> 20:54.795
in LA, you know?

20:55.629 --> 20:56.546
And...

20:56.755 --> 20:59.508
even though I was only here
for a few months, I mean...

20:59.591 --> 21:01.426
[speech rapidly quietens and echoes]

21:01.510 --> 21:04.638
[high-pitched tone ringing]

21:04.721 --> 21:07.182
[breathing heavily]

21:11.687 --> 21:15.399
[muted speech]

21:24.491 --> 21:25.659
[pages turning]

21:25.742 --> 21:26.785
[whooshing]

21:26.868 --> 21:28.912
[phone ringing]

21:32.624 --> 21:34.668
[at normal volume]
Well, it's great. We love it.

21:34.751 --> 21:36.670
And we'd love to do this with you.

21:36.753 --> 21:37.713
Awesome.

21:40.507 --> 21:42.843
Sorry, uh, what does that mean exactly?

21:42.926 --> 21:45.095
Uh, [stammers]
we'd like to make your movie.

21:45.178 --> 21:47.848
Uh,
so please don't sell it to anyone else.

21:48.056 --> 21:51.226
'Cause, um... Yeah. And we'll get
an official offer out, like, next week.

21:51.310 --> 21:52.769
Um, do you have an agent?

21:54.521 --> 21:56.398
[chuckles] Oh, my God!

21:56.481 --> 21:58.108
Did that just happen?

21:58.191 --> 22:01.528
I mean, is this what it feels like
when your entire life changes?

22:01.653 --> 22:04.531
[gasps] How much money do think
they're gonna give us?

22:04.614 --> 22:06.533
How do you... How do you get an agent?

22:07.075 --> 22:09.119
How are you so calm right now?

22:09.202 --> 22:12.205
Holy shit! I mean, we have to celebrate.
Where should we go?

22:12.456 --> 22:13.540
You know, I gotta...

22:14.416 --> 22:18.086
I gotta go see a guy about a thing.
Why don't you just take the car, and...

22:18.337 --> 22:19.838
and I'll get a cab, okay?

22:20.130 --> 22:21.465
-Seriously?
-[Sam] Yeah.

22:21.548 --> 22:23.633
What the fuck?
Who am I supposed to celebrate with?

22:23.717 --> 22:25.218
[Sam] I don't know. Billy?

22:25.302 --> 22:27.804
Uh, maybe some of the other people
you wrote the movie about?

22:27.888 --> 22:29.514
I don't fucking know.
I don't fucking know.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.142
What is your problem?

22:32.225 --> 22:34.353
You're being so weird right now.

22:34.770 --> 22:35.937
[Sam exhales]

22:40.442 --> 22:41.818
-He-Hey...
-[car door slams]

22:42.527 --> 22:43.612
Justine...

22:45.447 --> 22:46.573
-[sighs]
-What?

22:49.993 --> 22:52.913
I just want you to know that I'm...
I'm very proud of you.

22:53.747 --> 22:54.831
And I love you.

22:57.542 --> 23:00.879
Okay. Whatever. Love you, too.

23:02.756 --> 23:04.383
[car engine starts]

23:04.466 --> 23:07.177
[tense electronic music playing]

23:17.979 --> 23:20.524
[panting]

23:22.109 --> 23:23.360
-Hey-- Hey, buddy.
-[man] Yeah?

23:23.443 --> 23:25.070
Hey, can you call me an ambulance, please?

23:25.153 --> 23:27.447
-Call me an ambulance. Okay?
-[man] Yeah, sure. Sure.

23:28.281 --> 23:29.491
Ah, fuck.

23:31.368 --> 23:32.494
Ah, come on.

23:33.495 --> 23:34.454
Come on.

23:34.955 --> 23:35.997
[exhales]

23:36.665 --> 23:37.541
[man] Thank you.

23:39.292 --> 23:40.252
Thank you.

23:40.919 --> 23:43.046
[in hoarse voice] How many dresses
did you get? Are you okay?

23:43.130 --> 23:45.424
Marty, can you hear us?

23:45.590 --> 23:46.967
[Marty, over intercom]
<i>I'm here, Mrs. Howard.</i>

23:47.050 --> 23:48.760
Is that our business manager?<i></i>
[clears throat]

23:48.844 --> 23:51.096
[Allen] <i>And me. Allen. I’m here, too.</i>

23:51.179 --> 23:52.055
Who’s Allen?

23:52.139 --> 23:54.433
The family lawyer. What is this, a coup?

23:55.016 --> 23:57.060
[sighs] Darling, as much as I’d like it,

23:57.144 --> 23:59.980
you can’t be on an allowance forever.

24:00.522 --> 24:02.399
You’re a grown, married man now.

24:02.607 --> 24:03.483
I knew it!

24:04.067 --> 24:06.403
Fine! Cut me off!

24:06.653 --> 24:10.031
We’re doing great out here, Birdie.
We can support ourselves.

24:10.115 --> 24:13.493
You can’t banish us. I banish <i>you!</i>

24:13.785 --> 24:15.787
Oh, sit down,
you're embarrassing yourself.

24:15.871 --> 24:17.038
We’re not on <i>Falcon Crest.</i>

24:17.414 --> 24:18.790
So you do watch television.

24:20.584 --> 24:21.585
Marty?

24:22.043 --> 24:24.713
[Marty] <i>Sebastian, when your grandfather</i>
<i>set up your trust,</i>

24:24.796 --> 24:28.550
<i>he allowed for a stipulation</i>
<i>that if you were to be married,</i>

24:28.633 --> 24:32.888
<i>you would bypass your living trustees,</i>
<i>your, uh, mother in this case,</i>

24:32.971 --> 24:35.390
<i>and unlock the whole of your funds.</i>

24:37.392 --> 24:38.894
[clears throat] Meaning?

24:39.978 --> 24:42.689
[Allen] <i>This is Allen now.</i>
<i>The full 40 million dollars,</i>

24:42.772 --> 24:46.776
<i>including the assets of your inheritance,</i>
<i>are yours to do with what you’d like.</i>

24:47.402 --> 24:48.653
[exhales]

24:49.279 --> 24:50.572
Forty million dollars?

24:50.655 --> 24:52.657
[up-tempo electronic music playing]

24:54.659 --> 24:57.037
[Rhonda chuckles in disbelief]

24:58.538 --> 24:59.498
You’re joking.

24:59.581 --> 25:01.333
Oh, yes, I’m the comic relief.

25:05.462 --> 25:07.130
[chuckles]

25:09.049 --> 25:10.675
-Hold on, hold on.
-What?

25:12.385 --> 25:15.055
-See?
-[both chuckling]

25:15.764 --> 25:18.475
It's nice to be on a date with a grown-up
for a change.

25:18.558 --> 25:20.101
Sure, babies can be a handful.

25:20.310 --> 25:23.647
Yes, babies.
That's exactly who I was talking about.

25:23.897 --> 25:26.650
You know,
I think I missed out on that stage.

25:27.526 --> 25:28.818
How old are your boys?

25:29.486 --> 25:31.154
Twenty-four now,

25:31.446 --> 25:33.156
Uh, 20 and 18.

25:35.283 --> 25:36.409
I missed a lot of it.

25:37.911 --> 25:39.037
Uh, that’s on me, though.

25:39.120 --> 25:41.790
My ex is a good woman, excellent mother.

25:42.958 --> 25:45.794
She used to say I was overextended
and unfocused. Well...

25:46.545 --> 25:49.673
in truth, I’m just a... a dabbler.

25:50.006 --> 25:51.633
What do you dabble in, Tex?

25:52.467 --> 25:55.053
Well, I had a ranch. I have ranches.

25:55.136 --> 25:56.638
Oh, you’re a rancher.

25:56.721 --> 25:57.722
I'm not a rancher.

25:57.806 --> 26:00.308
I have this ranch,
and the ranch had a mine on it.

26:00.392 --> 26:03.937
And, long story short, that mine produced
a semiconductor that they use in radios,

26:04.396 --> 26:07.899
which led me to what you call media...

26:08.400 --> 26:11.361
but I like to call it
buying up little radio stations,

26:11.444 --> 26:13.738
and we’re in expansion mode now, so...

26:13.947 --> 26:15.490
-[exhales forcefully]
-[Debbie laughs]

26:15.574 --> 26:17.200
What do you do, Debbie?

26:17.534 --> 26:18.910
Um, the same.

26:19.035 --> 26:20.036
[both chuckle]

26:20.120 --> 26:22.872
No, I... I'm also a dabbler. Uh...

26:23.456 --> 26:25.333
I just make way less money.

26:25.417 --> 26:27.502
Um, I-- I'm a producer and an actress.

26:28.128 --> 26:29.045
Uh...

26:29.170 --> 26:30.630
And I'm a wrestler.

26:31.047 --> 26:31.881
Uh?

26:31.965 --> 26:34.426
-I, uh, produce a wrestling show.
-[laughs] What?

26:34.634 --> 26:37.887
At the Fan-Tan,
that I also happen to star in.

26:38.555 --> 26:41.099
You're having dinner with Liberty Belle,

26:41.182 --> 26:43.852
one of the Gorgeous Ladies Of Wrestling.

26:43.935 --> 26:45.395
Oh, my God!

26:45.478 --> 26:46.563
-[Debbie] Uh-huh.
-I thought I was sitting

26:46.646 --> 26:47.814
with somebody special.

26:47.897 --> 26:48.982
[both laugh]

26:49.065 --> 26:51.860
Yeah, well... No, I am...
I'm trying to-- to transition more

26:51.943 --> 26:54.446
into the producing side of things.
It's just, um...

26:55.655 --> 26:57.741
I don't know, it hasn't been easy. And...

26:57.907 --> 26:59.242
Especially with a kid.

27:00.285 --> 27:01.453
Mostly, I'm just...

27:01.661 --> 27:03.246
staring down the barrel of life,

27:03.330 --> 27:05.248
wondering what the hell
I'm aiming for, Tex.

27:06.666 --> 27:09.544
You know my name's not really...
Tex, right?

27:10.712 --> 27:11.796
Oh, my God.

27:12.297 --> 27:13.173
What?

27:13.632 --> 27:14.924
Why did I make up that name?

27:15.008 --> 27:17.510
I don't know, the hat, or the accent,
or some such.

27:17.594 --> 27:19.012
You're an imaginative woman.

27:19.095 --> 27:21.598
-I’m actually from Wyoming.
-[laughing] No, no, no!

27:21.681 --> 27:23.683
Yeah, up the street. Yeah.

27:23.975 --> 27:26.019
-[laughs] Oh, my God. Jesus.
-Ah...

27:27.687 --> 27:28.647
What's your name?

27:28.730 --> 27:30.732
It's... But... James.

27:30.857 --> 27:33.401
-No.
-James Joseph McCready. JJ.

27:33.485 --> 27:35.153
Okay. I'm gonna go.

27:35.612 --> 27:37.155
-No, stay.
-[laughs]

27:37.238 --> 27:40.492
-Okay, people call you JJ?
-They call me JJ. They do.

27:40.575 --> 27:41.534
God.

27:43.578 --> 27:45.246
Can I still call you Tex?

27:47.040 --> 27:48.833
You can call me whatever you want.

27:51.211 --> 27:53.213
[monitor beeping]

27:56.299 --> 27:57.592
Okay, Mr. Sylvia,

27:57.676 --> 28:01.346
so the results from your EKG confirm
that you've had a cardiac event.

28:03.598 --> 28:04.766
Just say heart attack.

28:06.518 --> 28:07.977
Yes. A heart attack.

28:09.396 --> 28:11.064
Believe it or not, you’re lucky.

28:11.523 --> 28:13.233
But consider this a wake-up call.

28:13.566 --> 28:16.611
At your age, it’s time to start laying off
the alcohol and cigarettes.

28:16.695 --> 28:19.155
You’ll have to change your diet,
start exercising.

28:19.698 --> 28:22.117
That’s what I've been doing.
I've been doing that.

28:22.200 --> 28:24.202
Well, then you're on the right path.

28:24.703 --> 28:27.038
We’re gonna keep you overnight
for observation, all right?

28:27.455 --> 28:28.998
Is there anyone you want us to call?

28:30.834 --> 28:31.960
[sighs]

28:34.504 --> 28:35.547
No.

28:42.887 --> 28:44.180
[Birdie] As soon as I get back,

28:44.264 --> 28:46.683
I’ll put you in touch
with our group at Morgan Stanley.

28:46.766 --> 28:48.309
We’ll get your portfolio all set up.

28:48.685 --> 28:50.562
Eventually, you’re gonna need a will.

28:50.645 --> 28:53.064
[sighs] Always thinking ahead.

28:53.481 --> 28:54.566
Thank you, Birdie.

28:58.570 --> 28:59.404
What's happening?

29:01.948 --> 29:03.074
You're married.

29:04.492 --> 29:06.244
[chuckles softly] I am.

29:09.497 --> 29:12.250
I didn’t feel a thing
at your sister’s wedding, but...

29:14.085 --> 29:15.712
I think I would have at yours.

29:20.049 --> 29:22.093
Well, we can always do something
when I get back.

29:22.552 --> 29:24.679
Oh, we will.
If you think you’re getting away

29:24.763 --> 29:27.098
without me throwing a giant party
that you’ll hate,

29:27.182 --> 29:28.475
you're out of your mind.

29:30.393 --> 29:32.645
Consider having children
while I’m still young enough

29:32.729 --> 29:34.522
to be mistaken for their mother.

29:34.606 --> 29:35.690
[chuckles]

29:38.860 --> 29:41.488
-Thank you so much for everything.
-Oh.

29:42.155 --> 29:43.531
And for making Bash.

29:45.283 --> 29:46.618
Oh. [chuckles]

29:51.331 --> 29:52.916
Keep him interested.

29:57.212 --> 29:59.464
However you see fit.

30:03.301 --> 30:04.511
[car door opens]

30:05.470 --> 30:06.429
[car door closes]

30:06.554 --> 30:08.556
[car engine starts]

30:09.432 --> 30:11.059
Thank you. Thank you.

30:12.560 --> 30:13.436
Um...

30:13.937 --> 30:18.983
How’s about... you come back to my hotel,
and I buy you that drink?

30:20.235 --> 30:22.111
You’re always trying to get me drunk.

30:22.445 --> 30:23.279
Yeah.

30:23.780 --> 30:26.783
How about, instead of a drink tonight,

30:27.742 --> 30:28.868
you let me...

30:29.452 --> 30:31.120
take you out again tomorrow?

30:33.623 --> 30:37.293
That’s moving a little fast for me,
Tex from Wyoming.

30:38.044 --> 30:40.797
-You just invited me to your hotel.
-Oh, yeah.

30:57.313 --> 30:59.816
-I like kissing wrestlers.
-[laughs]

31:00.984 --> 31:02.861
-Okay. Tomorrow night.
-Okay.

31:04.279 --> 31:06.281
[gentle acoustic music playing]

31:50.825 --> 31:52.827
[water pouring]

31:53.411 --> 31:54.829
[Justine] Jesus Christ.

31:56.664 --> 31:57.749
What the hell?

31:58.499 --> 32:00.627
I was about to call the police.
Where were you?

32:05.632 --> 32:06.674
Sorry.

32:07.050 --> 32:08.635
Old habits die hard.

32:09.302 --> 32:11.304
[Justine] You're such a bastard.

32:11.554 --> 32:13.765
I wanted to celebrate with you.

32:13.848 --> 32:16.059
Instead, I had the worst night with Billy.

32:16.142 --> 32:17.101
Oh, yeah?

32:17.602 --> 32:19.437
-How's Billy?
-Fat.

32:19.938 --> 32:23.191
I mean, still cute,
but he definitely put on a few.

32:23.274 --> 32:25.860
And he dragged me to some terrible club
that smelled like feet,

32:25.944 --> 32:28.655
and I ended up helping some girl
look for her purse for, like, an hour.

32:29.238 --> 32:32.450
-Yeah? You should put that in your movie.
-[Justine] Our movie.

32:33.701 --> 32:34.577
No.

32:35.161 --> 32:36.537
It's your journey now, kid.

32:38.665 --> 32:41.042
So, what? You don't want to direct it?

32:44.170 --> 32:45.546
What are you talking about?

32:45.630 --> 32:47.507
[scoffs] I fucking knew it.

32:47.590 --> 32:50.510
You were so wrapped up
in your old shit with what’s-his-face,

32:50.593 --> 32:54.681
the Zen prick, you weren’t even listening.
And you want me to give a shit? Okay, man.

32:55.890 --> 32:56.891
What?

32:58.601 --> 32:59.435
What?

32:59.936 --> 33:02.271
I told that guy I wouldn’t do it
without you directing.

33:02.438 --> 33:03.648
Why would you say that?

33:03.731 --> 33:06.025
[Justine] Will you calm down?
What is the matter with you?

33:06.109 --> 33:07.485
I can't fucking direct.

33:07.568 --> 33:10.321
I haven’t directed anything good in years.
I mean, maybe ever.

33:10.405 --> 33:13.199
Bullshit! And... too bad.

33:13.491 --> 33:16.452
Justine, you don’t have to bring me
with you, all right? I’m dead weight.

33:16.536 --> 33:19.706
So, you can believe in me,
but I can’t believe in you?

33:19.789 --> 33:22.834
I-- I-- I wrote a movie,
I sold that movie,

33:22.917 --> 33:25.420
I demanded you direct that movie, so...

33:25.712 --> 33:27.505
we’re making that fucking movie!

33:27.588 --> 33:28.423
Together.

33:28.506 --> 33:31.342
[stammers] Or at least until we both
get found out and fired.

33:31.592 --> 33:33.177
Jesus Christ!

33:35.638 --> 33:37.140
We should celebrate!

33:41.352 --> 33:42.353
-Yeah!
-[glasses clink]

33:43.104 --> 33:46.441
That’s what I’ve been trying to say, jerk.

33:48.151 --> 33:49.736
-We're making a movie.
-[Justine laughs]

33:49.819 --> 33:52.697
-Yeah, we're making a movie.
-[pouring drinks]

33:57.577 --> 33:58.494
[glasses clink]

34:00.413 --> 34:01.372
[sighs]

34:05.293 --> 34:08.796
Mm! [exhales

